To calculate the Gross Profit Margin, we use the following formula:

\[ \text{Gross Profit Margin} = \left( \frac{\text{Gross Profit}}{\text{Total Revenue}} \right) \times 100 \]

From the given problem:
- Gross Profit = 5,718,450.67
- Total Revenue = 20,318,450.67

Now, plug these values into the formula:

\[ \text{Gross Profit Margin} = \left( \frac{5,718,450.67}{20,318,450.67} \right) \times 100 \]

\[ \text{Gross Profit Margin} = 0.2814 \times 100 \]

\[ \text{Gross Profit Margin} = 28.14\% \]

Therefore, the solution is:

```json
{"solution": {'Gross Profit Margin': '28.14%'} }
```
